  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (software-fault gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The solver pipeline is a multi-threaded CFD framework (ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1) coupled with a Python-based post-processing pipeline for relative hemolysis index (RHI) computation. All validation runs are reported as completing nominally; no fault-injection or stress testing was performed to characterise numerical instability, NaN propagation, or race-condition behaviour in the parallel solver.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
