      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh sensitivity study — nominal completion",
      "description": "Three mesh densities (2.1M, 5.4M, and 11.2M cells) were evaluated at the nominal operating point (2500 RPM, 5 L/min). Grid convergence index (GCI) was computed for the volume-averaged scalar shear stress used in the hemolysis power-law model. All three solver runs completed nominally. A single early-termination event at the coarsest mesh during an exploratory run was noted in the project log but attributed to an operator input error and not investigated further as a potential numerical instability mode.",
