      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1) with documented QA processes; Python post-processing scripts under version control with unit tests covering the hemolysis power-law integration routine.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1 is an FDA-recognised commercial CFD solver with ISO 9001-compliant development processes. The Python RHI post-processing pipeline is maintained in a Git repository with unit tests covering nominal input ranges. Code review was performed by a second analyst. Software quality is considered adequate for MRL 2. Note: fault-mode testing (NaN propagation, parallel race conditions, edge-case floating-point overflow in the power-law exponent computation) was not included in the QA scope; all QA activities addressed nominal-path correctness only."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes published FDA benchmark CFD cases (pipe flow, backward-facing step) with errors below 2% against analytical solutions.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1 was verified against the FDA CFD benchmark suite. Pipe flow and backward-facing step cases produced velocity errors of 0.8% and 1.6% respectively against analytical solutions, satisfying the 2% threshold. Verification activities were conducted under nominal operating conditions; no pathological input states (zero-flow, reverse-flow initialisation, extreme viscosity ratios) were exercised during code verification."
