      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Bench test fluid properties (viscosity, density) match CFD boundary conditions within 5%; temperature controlled to 37 ± 0.5 °C.",
      "rationale": "Bench haemolysis experiments were conducted with porcine blood at 37 ± 0.3 °C. Measured viscosity (3.2 mPa·s) and density (1055 kg/m³) matched CFD inputs within 2%. Flow rates were controlled by a calibrated peristaltic pump with ±1.5% accuracy. Test conditions are considered well-matched to the simulation inputs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RHI within 15% of measured values across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted RHI values ranged from 0.61 to 0.94 against measured bench values of 0.58 to 0.97. Maximum absolute deviation was 9.3% at the 3500 RPM, 3 L/min operating point, within the 15% acceptance criterion. Output comparison was performed exclusively on converged nominal runs; no comparison was made for any partially-converged or fault-affected solver states."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Volume-averaged scalar shear stress and exposure-time-integrated hemolysis index are directly linked to the RH acceptance criterion used in the regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (relative hemolysis index, RHI) is directly used in the regulatory comparison against the predicate device. The power-law hemolysis model integrates scalar shear stress and exposure time along Lagrangian particle tracks, which are physically meaningful surrogates for erythrocyte damage. The QoI chain from solver output to regulatory decision is well-documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
