      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments cover the full operating envelope (5 flow-speed combinations) specified in the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments were conducted at all five flow-speed combinations (1500–3500 RPM, 3–7 L/min) specified in the COU. The FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry used in validation is geometrically representative of the Class II CPB device under assessment. Validation activities are considered directly relevant to the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence to residuals below 1e-5 for all governing equations; mass imbalance below 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "All production simulation runs achieved residual convergence below 1e-5 for continuity, momentum, and turbulence equations. Global mass imbalance was below 0.005% in all cases. Convergence histories were reviewed by the lead analyst. One early-termination event during exploratory meshing was noted in the project log and attributed to an operator input error; this event was not subjected to root-cause analysis to determine whether numerical instability (e.g., divergence triggered by high aspect-ratio cells near the impeller tip) was a contributing factor."
    },
