      "acceptanceCriteria": "SST k-omega turbulence model and Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model are appropriate for the Reynolds number range and shear stress levels encountered in the CPB pump.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model is well-validated for rotating machinery flows at the Reynolds numbers encountered (Re 4,000–18,000). The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is widely used in FDA pump assessments and has been validated against in-vitro data for similar shear stress magnitudes (1–100 Pa). Model form uncertainty is considered acceptable at MRL 2."
