    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The six remaining factors are not assessed, which is acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. Validation results across all four validation activities demonstrate nominal solver completion, adequate output agreement (maximum RHI deviation 9.3%), and appropriate mesh convergence (GCI 1.8%). The CFD-Python pipeline produces RHI predictions satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion at all five COU operating points. The credibility package is accepted as sufficient to support the regulatory submission for the Class II CPB device.",
